@yrqls21 Mainly: it works with Python 2, and is a cleaner code base. Also Dropbox seems (emphasis on seems) a bit more involved there.

@laserson (who contributed a lot to Impyla especially at the beginning) seems not be active in the repo anymore, and @wesm, who also contributed a lot, has since left Cloudera. 

The project went without commits (besides a bump) for more than a year, while the number of issues is growing.

@Fokko @yrqls21   PTAL. In my previous PR [AIRFLOW-2581](https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/pull/3482), I changed the default value of
autocommit to True in DbApiHook.run(), which may cause some performance
issues, so I changed it back to False.

@feng-tao I request you to not open/close the PR to trigger the travis CI. If you want to run the build again please run travis CI on your cloned repo as Travis would be free and give us the link for the build.

We have been warned by Apache Infra team regarding the consumption of CPU time as they pay for it.

Thanks.

I was misunderstanding what `should_commit` was for and thus [this change](https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/pull/3485) doesn't completely fix the failing CI (~not sure why the CI passed in the PR tho~ cuz [this PR](https://github.com/apache/incubator-airflow/pull/3487) was created afterwards and merged before my PR was merged).

@imroc, I'm basically reverting your change, I don't see why it was not working for you before your change. Can you elaborate please? Thank you

@Fokko @bolkedebruin @artwr @kaxil @feng-tao PTAL
